The paper deals with the classification of cryptographic primitives in compiled binary executables using deep learning, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of deep learning algorithms for this purpose suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the procedural generation of synthetic cryptographic binaries, which may fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the threat of crypto-ransomware, which is a type of cybercrime, suggesting that it may also belong to the category of cyber security (cs.CY).
